---
description: Security and dependency remediation standards for Superset
globs: ["requirements/*.txt", "pyproject.toml", "superset-frontend/package.json"]
alwaysApply: false
---

When remediating a flagged dependency in Superset:
- Superset has two independent dependency surfaces — Python (requirements/*.txt,
  pyproject.toml) and the frontend (superset-frontend/package.json). Identify
  which surface is affected before proposing a fix.
- Never silently upgrade a major version — flag it and explain the breaking
  change risk. Versions here are tightly pinned for a reason; pandas, pyarrow,
  and flask-appbuilder versions are load-bearing for the data layer.
- Always check internal usage via codebase search before patching.
- Never touch superset/security/ or SQL Lab execution paths without
  flagging for human review first.
- Any patches to Python dependencies must remain MyPy compliant and follow
  the type hint standards in dev-standard.mdc.
